var book = {
	"name": "Daniel",
	"numChapters": 12,
	"chapters": {
		"1": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">1 </span>In the third year of the reign of Jehoiakim<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-21739A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-21739A\"></sup> king of Judah, Nebuchadnezzar<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-21739B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-21739B\"></sup> king of Babylon<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-21739C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-21739C\"></sup> came to Jerusalem and besieged it.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-21739D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-21739D\"></sup>",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>And the Lord delivered Jehoiakim king of Judah into his hand, along with some of the articles from the temple of God. These he carried<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-21740E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-21740E\"></sup> off to the temple of his god in Babylonia and put in the treasure house of his god.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-21740F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-21740F\"></sup>",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>Then the king ordered Ashpenaz, chief of his court officials, to bring into the king’s service some of the Israelites from the royal family and the nobility<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-21741G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-21741G\"></sup>—",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>young men without any physical defect, handsome,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-21742H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-21742H\"></sup> showing aptitude for every kind of learning,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-21742I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-21742I\"></sup> well informed, quick to understand, and qualified to serve in the king’s palace. He was to teach them the language<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-21742J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-21742J\"></sup> and literature of the Babylonians.",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>The king assigned them a daily amount of food and wine<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-21743K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-21743K\"></sup> from the king’s table.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-21743L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-21743L\"></sup> They were to be trained for three years,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-21743M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-21743M\"></sup> and after that they were to enter the king’s service.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-21743N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-21743N\"></sup>",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>Among those who were chosen were some from Judah: Daniel,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-21744O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-21744O\"></sup> Hananiah, Mishael and Azariah.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-21744P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-21744P\"></sup>",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>The chief official gave them new names: to Daniel, the name Belteshazzar;<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-21745Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-21745Q\"></sup> to Hananiah, Shadrach; to Mishael, Meshach; and to Azariah, Abednego.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-21745R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-21745R\"></sup>",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>But Daniel resolved not to defile<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-21746S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-21746S\"></sup> himself with the royal food and wine, and he asked the chief official for permission not to defile himself this way.",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>Now God had caused the official to show favor<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-21747T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-21747T\"></sup> and compassion<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-21747U&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference U&quot;&gt;U&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-21747U\"></sup> to Daniel,",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>but the official told Daniel, “I am afraid of my lord the king, who has assigned your food and drink.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-21748V&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference V&quot;&gt;V&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-21748V\"></sup> Why should he see you looking worse than the other young men your age? The king would then have my head because of you.”",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>Daniel then said to the guard whom the chief official had appointed over Daniel, Hananiah, Mishael and Azariah,",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>“Please test<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-21750W&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference W&quot;&gt;W&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-21750W\"></sup> your servants for ten days: Give us nothing but vegetables to eat and water to drink.",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>Then compare our appearance with that of the young men who eat the royal food, and treat your servants in accordance with what you see.”<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-21751X&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference X&quot;&gt;X&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-21751X\"></sup>",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>So he agreed to this and tested<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-21752Y&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Y&quot;&gt;Y&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-21752Y\"></sup> them for ten days.",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>At the end of the ten days they looked healthier and better nourished than any of the young men who ate the royal food.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-21753Z&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Z&quot;&gt;Z&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-21753Z\"></sup>",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>So the guard took away their choice food and the wine they were to drink and gave them vegetables instead.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-21754AA&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AA&quot;&gt;AA&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-21754AA\"></sup>",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>To these four young men God gave knowledge and understanding<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-21755AB&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AB&quot;&gt;AB&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-21755AB\"></sup> of all kinds of literature and learning.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-21755AC&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AC&quot;&gt;AC&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-21755AC\"></sup> And Daniel could understand visions and dreams of all kinds.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-21755AD&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AD&quot;&gt;AD&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-21755AD\"></sup>",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>At the end of the time<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-21756AE&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AE&quot;&gt;AE&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-21756AE\"></sup> set by the king to bring them into his service, the chief official presented them to Nebuchadnezzar.",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>The king talked with them, and he found none equal to Daniel, Hananiah, Mishael and Azariah; so they entered the king’s service.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-21757AF&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AF&quot;&gt;AF&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-21757AF\"></sup>",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup>In every matter of wisdom and understanding about which the king questioned them, he found them ten times better than all the magicians<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-21758AG&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AG&quot;&gt;AG&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-21758AG\"></sup> and enchanters in his whole kingdom.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-21758AH&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AH&quot;&gt;AH&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-21758AH\"></sup>",
			"21": "<sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup>And Daniel remained there until the first year of King Cyrus.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-21759AI&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AI&quot;&gt;AI&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-21759AI\"></sup>"
		},
		"2": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">2 </span>In the second year of his reign, Nebuchadnezzar had dreams;<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-21760A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-21760A\"></sup> his mind was troubled<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-21760B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-21760B\"></sup> and he could not sleep.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-21760C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-21760C\"></sup>",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>So the king summoned the magicians,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-21761D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-21761D\"></sup> enchanters, sorcerers<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-21761E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-21761E\"></sup> and astrologers<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-21761F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-21761F\"></sup> to tell him what he had dreamed.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-21761G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-21761G\"></sup> When they came in and stood before the king,",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>he said to them, “I have had a dream that troubles<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-21762H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-21762H\"></sup> me and I want to know what it means.”",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>Then the astrologers answered the king,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-21763I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-21763I\"></sup> “May the king live forever!<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-21763J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-21763J\"></sup> Tell your servants the dream, and we will interpret it.”",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>The king replied to the astrologers, “This is what I have firmly decided:<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-21764K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-21764K\"></sup> If you do not tell me what my dream was and interpret it, I will have you cut into pieces<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-21764L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-21764L\"></sup> and your houses turned into piles of rubble.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-21764M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-21764M\"></sup>",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>But if you tell me the dream and explain it, you will receive from me gifts and rewards and great honor.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-21765N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-21765N\"></sup> So tell me the dream and interpret it for me.”",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>Once more they replied, “Let the king tell his servants the dream, and we will interpret it.”",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>Then the king answered, “I am certain that you are trying to gain time, because you realize that this is what I have firmly decided:",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>If you do not tell me the dream, there is only one penalty<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-21768O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-21768O\"></sup> for you. You have conspired to tell me misleading and wicked things, hoping the situation will change. So then, tell me the dream, and I will know that you can interpret it for me.”<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-21768P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-21768P\"></sup>",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>The astrologers<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-21769Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-21769Q\"></sup> answered the king, “There is no one on earth who can do what the king asks! No king, however great and mighty, has ever asked such a thing of any magician or enchanter or astrologer.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-21769R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-21769R\"></sup>",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>What the king asks is too difficult. No one can reveal it to the king except the gods,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-21770S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-21770S\"></sup> and they do not live among humans.”",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>This made the king so angry and furious<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-21771T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-21771T\"></sup> that he ordered the execution<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-21771U&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference U&quot;&gt;U&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-21771U\"></sup> of all the wise men of Babylon.",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>So the decree was issued to put the wise men to death, and men were sent to look for Daniel and his friends to put them to death.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-21772V&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference V&quot;&gt;V&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-21772V\"></sup>",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>When Arioch, the commander of the king’s guard, had gone out to put to death the wise men of Babylon, Daniel spoke to him with wisdom and tact.",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>He asked the king’s officer, “Why did the king issue such a harsh decree?” Arioch then explained the matter to Daniel.",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>At this, Daniel went in to the king and asked for time, so that he might interpret the dream for him.",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>Then Daniel returned to his house and explained the matter to his friends Hananiah, Mishael and Azariah.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-21776W&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference W&quot;&gt;W&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-21776W\"></sup>",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>He urged them to plead for mercy<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-21777X&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference X&quot;&gt;X&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-21777X\"></sup> from the God of heaven<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-21777Y&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Y&quot;&gt;Y&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-21777Y\"></sup> concerning this mystery,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-21777Z&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Z&quot;&gt;Z&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-21777Z\"></sup> so that he and his friends might not be executed with the rest of the wise men of Babylon.",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>During the night the mystery<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-21778AA&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AA&quot;&gt;AA&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-21778AA\"></sup> was revealed to Daniel in a vision.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-21778AB&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AB&quot;&gt;AB&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-21778AB\"></sup> Then Daniel praised the God of heaven<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-21778AC&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AC&quot;&gt;AC&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-21778AC\"></sup>",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup>and said:“Praise be to the name of God for ever and ever;<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-21779AD&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AD&quot;&gt;AD&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-21779AD\"></sup>wisdom and power<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-21779AE&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AE&quot;&gt;AE&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-21779AE\"></sup> are his.",
			"21": "<sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup>He changes times and seasons;<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-21780AF&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AF&quot;&gt;AF&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-21780AF\"></sup>he deposes<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-21780AG&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AG&quot;&gt;AG&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-21780AG\"></sup> kings and raises up others.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-21780AH&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AH&quot;&gt;AH&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-21780AH\"></sup>He gives wisdom<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-21780AI&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AI&quot;&gt;AI&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-21780AI\"></sup> to the wiseand knowledge to the discerning.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-21780AJ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AJ&quot;&gt;AJ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-21780AJ\"></sup>",
			"22": "<sup class=\"versenum\">22 </sup>He reveals deep and hidden things;<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-21781AK&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AK&quot;&gt;AK&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-21781AK\"></sup>he knows what lies in darkness,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-21781AL&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AL&quot;&gt;AL&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-21781AL\"></sup>and light<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-21781AM&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AM&quot;&gt;AM&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-21781AM\"></sup> dwells with him.",
			"23": "<sup class=\"versenum\">23 </sup>I thank and praise you, God of my ancestors:<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-21782AN&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AN&quot;&gt;AN&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-21782AN\"></sup>You have given me wisdom<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-21782AO&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AO&quot;&gt;AO&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-21782AO\"></sup> and power,you have made known to me what we asked of you,you have made known to us the dream of the king.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-21782AP&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AP&quot;&gt;AP&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-21782AP\"></sup>”",
			"24": "<sup class=\"versenum\">24 </sup>Then Daniel went to Arioch,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-21783AQ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AQ&quot;&gt;AQ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-21783AQ\"></sup> whom the king had appointed to execute the wise men of Babylon, and said to him, “Do not execute the wise men of Babylon. Take me to the king, and I will interpret his dream for him.”",
			"25": "<sup class=\"versenum\">25 </sup>Arioch took Daniel to the king at once and said, “I have found a man among the exiles<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-21784AR&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AR&quot;&gt;AR&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-21784AR\"></sup> from Judah<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-21784AS&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AS&quot;&gt;AS&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-21784AS\"></sup> who can tell the king what his dream means.”",
			"26": "<sup class=\"versenum\">26 </sup>The king asked Daniel (also called Belteshazzar),<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-21785AT&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AT&quot;&gt;AT&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-21785AT\"></sup> “Are you able to tell me what I saw in my dream and interpret it?”",
			"27": "<sup class=\"versenum\">27 </sup>Daniel replied, “No wise man, enchanter, magician or diviner can explain to the king the mystery he has asked about,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-21786AU&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AU&quot;&gt;AU&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-21786AU\"></sup>",
			"28": "<sup class=\"versenum\">28 </sup>but there is a God in heaven who reveals mysteries.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-21787AV&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AV&quot;&gt;AV&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-21787AV\"></sup> He has shown King Nebuchadnezzar what will happen in days to come.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-21787AW&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AW&quot;&gt;AW&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-21787AW\"></sup> Your dream and the visions that passed through your mind<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-21787AX&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AX&quot;&gt;AX&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-21787AX\"></sup> as you were lying in bed<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-21787AY&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AY&quot;&gt;AY&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-21787AY\"></sup> are these:<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-21787AZ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AZ&quot;&gt;AZ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-21787AZ\"></sup>",
			"29": "<sup class=\"versenum\">29 </sup>“As Your Majesty was lying there, your mind turned to things to come, and the revealer of mysteries showed you what is going to happen.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-21788BA&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BA&quot;&gt;BA&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-21788BA\"></sup>",
			"30": "<sup class=\"versenum\">30 </sup>As for me, this mystery has been revealed<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-21789BB&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BB&quot;&gt;BB&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-21789BB\"></sup> to me, not because I have greater wisdom than anyone else alive, but so that Your Majesty may know the interpretation and that you may understand what went through your mind.",
			"31": "<sup class=\"versenum\">31 </sup>“Your Majesty looked, and there before you stood a large statue—an enormous, dazzling statue,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-21790BC&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BC&quot;&gt;BC&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-21790BC\"></sup> awesome<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-21790BD&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BD&quot;&gt;BD&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-21790BD\"></sup> in appearance.",
			"32": "<sup class=\"versenum\">32 </sup>The head of the statue was made of pure gold, its chest and arms of silver, its belly and thighs of bronze,",
			"33": "<sup class=\"versenum\">33 </sup>its legs of iron, its feet partly of iron and partly of baked clay.",
			"34": "<sup class=\"versenum\">34 </sup>While you were watching, a rock was cut out, but not by human hands.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-21793BE&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BE&quot;&gt;BE&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-21793BE\"></sup> It struck the statue on its feet of iron and clay and smashed<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-21793BF&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BF&quot;&gt;BF&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-21793BF\"></sup> them.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-21793BG&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BG&quot;&gt;BG&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-21793BG\"></sup>",
			"35": "<sup class=\"versenum\">35 </sup>Then the iron, the clay, the bronze, the silver and the gold were all broken to pieces and became like chaff on a threshing floor in the summer. The wind swept them away<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-21794BH&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BH&quot;&gt;BH&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-21794BH\"></sup> without leaving a trace. But the rock that struck the statue became a huge mountain<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-21794BI&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BI&quot;&gt;BI&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-21794BI\"></sup> and filled the whole earth.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-21794BJ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BJ&quot;&gt;BJ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-21794BJ\"></sup>",
			"36": "<sup class=\"versenum\">36 </sup>“This was the dream, and now we will interpret it to the king.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-21795BK&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BK&quot;&gt;BK&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-21795BK\"></sup>",
			"37": "<sup class=\"versenum\">37 </sup>Your Majesty, you are the king of kings.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-21796BL&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BL&quot;&gt;BL&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-21796BL\"></sup> The God of heaven has given you dominion<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-21796BM&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BM&quot;&gt;BM&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-21796BM\"></sup> and power and might and glory;",
			"38": "<sup class=\"versenum\">38 </sup>in your hands he has placed all mankind and the beasts of the field and the birds in the sky. Wherever they live, he has made you ruler over them all.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-21797BN&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BN&quot;&gt;BN&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-21797BN\"></sup> You are that head of gold.",
			"39": "<sup class=\"versenum\">39 </sup>“After you, another kingdom will arise, inferior to yours. Next, a third kingdom, one of bronze, will rule over the whole earth.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-21798BO&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BO&quot;&gt;BO&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-21798BO\"></sup>",
			"40": "<sup class=\"versenum\">40 </sup>Finally, there will be a fourth kingdom, strong as iron—for iron breaks and smashes everything—and as iron breaks things to pieces, so it will crush and break all the others.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-21799BP&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BP&quot;&gt;BP&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-21799BP\"></sup>",
			"41": "<sup class=\"versenum\">41 </sup>Just as you saw that the feet and toes were partly of baked clay and partly of iron, so this will be a divided kingdom; yet it will have some of the strength of iron in it, even as you saw iron mixed with clay.",
			"42": "<sup class=\"versenum\">42 </sup>As the toes were partly iron and partly clay, so this kingdom will be partly strong and partly brittle.",
			"43": "<sup class=\"versenum\">43 </sup>And just as you saw the iron mixed with baked clay, so the people will be a mixture and will not remain united, any more than iron mixes with clay.",
			"44": "<sup class=\"versenum\">44 </sup>“In the time of those kings, the God of heaven will set up a kingdom that will never be destroyed, nor will it be left to another people. It will crush<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-21803BQ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BQ&quot;&gt;BQ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-21803BQ\"></sup> all those kingdoms<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-21803BR&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BR&quot;&gt;BR&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-21803BR\"></sup> and bring them to an end, but it will itself endure forever.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-21803BS&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BS&quot;&gt;BS&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-21803BS\"></sup>",
			"45": "<sup class=\"versenum\">45 </sup>This is the meaning of the vision of the rock<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-21804BT&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BT&quot;&gt;BT&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-21804BT\"></sup> cut out of a mountain, but not by human hands<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-21804BU&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BU&quot;&gt;BU&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-21804BU\"></sup>—a rock that broke the iron, the bronze, the clay, the silver and the gold to pieces.“The great God has shown the king what will take place in the future.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-21804BV&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BV&quot;&gt;BV&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-21804BV\"></sup> The dream is true<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-21804BW&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BW&quot;&gt;BW&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-21804BW\"></sup> and its interpretation is trustworthy.”",
			"46": "<sup class=\"versenum\">46 </sup>Then King Nebuchadnezzar fell prostrate<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-21805BX&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BX&quot;&gt;BX&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-21805BX\"></sup> before Daniel and paid him honor and ordered that an offering<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-21805BY&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BY&quot;&gt;BY&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-21805BY\"></sup> and incense be presented to him.",
			"47": "<sup class=\"versenum\">47 </sup>The king said to Daniel, “Surely your God is the God of gods<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-21806BZ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BZ&quot;&gt;BZ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-21806BZ\"></sup> and the Lord of kings<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-21806CA&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference CA&quot;&gt;CA&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-21806CA\"></sup> and a revealer of mysteries,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-21806CB&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference CB&quot;&gt;CB&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-21806CB\"></sup> for you were able to reveal this mystery.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-21806CC&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference CC&quot;&gt;CC&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-21806CC\"></sup>”",
			"48": "<sup class=\"versenum\">48 </sup>Then the king placed Daniel in a high<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-21807CD&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference CD&quot;&gt;CD&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-21807CD\"></sup> position and lavished many gifts on him. He made him ruler over the entire province of Babylon and placed him in charge of all its wise men.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-21807CE&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference CE&quot;&gt;CE&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-21807CE\"></sup>",
			"49": "<sup class=\"versenum\">49 </sup>Moreover, at Daniel’s request the king appointed Shadrach, Meshach and Abednego administrators over the province of Babylon,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-21808CF&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference CF&quot;&gt;CF&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-21808CF\"></sup> while Daniel himself remained at the royal court.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-21808CG&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference CG&quot;&gt;CG&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-21808CG\"></sup>"
		},
		"3": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">3 </span>King Nebuchadnezzar made an image<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-21809A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-21809A\"></sup> of gold, sixty cubits high and six cubits wide, and set it up on the plain of Dura in the province of Babylon.",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>He then summoned the satraps,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-21810B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-21810B\"></sup> prefects, governors, advisers, treasurers, judges, magistrates and all the other provincial officials<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-21810C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-21810C\"></sup> to come to the dedication of the image he had set up.",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>So the satraps, prefects, governors, advisers, treasurers, judges, magistrates and all the other provincial officials assembled for the dedication of the image that King Nebuchadnezzar had set up, and they stood before it.",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>Then the herald loudly proclaimed, “Nations and peoples of every language,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-21812D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-21812D\"></sup> this is what you are commanded to do:",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>As soon as you hear the sound of the horn, flute, zither, lyre, harp,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-21813E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-21813E\"></sup> pipe and all kinds of music, you must fall down and worship the image<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-21813F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-21813F\"></sup> of gold that King Nebuchadnezzar has set up.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-21813G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-21813G\"></sup>",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>Whoever does not fall down and worship will immediately be thrown into a blazing furnace.”<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-21814H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-21814H\"></sup>",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>Therefore, as soon as they heard the sound of the horn, flute, zither, lyre, harp and all kinds of music, all the nations and peoples of every language fell down and worshiped the image of gold that King Nebuchadnezzar had set up.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-21815I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-21815I\"></sup>",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>At this time some astrologers<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-21816J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-21816J\"></sup> came forward and denounced the Jews.",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>They said to King Nebuchadnezzar, “May the king live forever!<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-21817K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-21817K\"></sup>",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>Your Majesty has issued a decree<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-21818L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-21818L\"></sup> that everyone who hears the sound of the horn, flute, zither, lyre, harp, pipe and all kinds of music must fall down and worship the image of gold,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-21818M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-21818M\"></sup>",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>and that whoever does not fall down and worship will be thrown into a blazing furnace.",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>But there are some Jews whom you have set over the affairs of the province of Babylon—Shadrach, Meshach and Abednego<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-21820N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-21820N\"></sup>—who pay no attention<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-21820O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-21820O\"></sup> to you, Your Majesty. They neither serve your gods nor worship the image of gold you have set up.”<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-21820P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-21820P\"></sup>",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>Furious<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-21821Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-21821Q\"></sup> with rage, Nebuchadnezzar summoned Shadrach, Meshach and Abednego. So these men were brought before the king,",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>and Nebuchadnezzar said to them, “Is it true, Shadrach, Meshach and Abednego, that you do not serve my gods<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-21822R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-21822R\"></sup> or worship the image<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-21822S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-21822S\"></sup> of gold I have set up?",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>Now when you hear the sound of the horn, flute, zither, lyre, harp, pipe and all kinds of music, if you are ready to fall down and worship the image I made, very good. But if you do not worship it, you will be thrown immediately into a blazing furnace. Then what god<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-21823T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-21823T\"></sup> will be able to rescue<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-21823U&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference U&quot;&gt;U&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-21823U\"></sup> you from my hand?”",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>Shadrach, Meshach and Abednego<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-21824V&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference V&quot;&gt;V&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-21824V\"></sup> replied to him, “King Nebuchadnezzar, we do not need to defend ourselves before you in this matter.",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>If we are thrown into the blazing furnace, the God we serve is able to deliver<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-21825W&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference W&quot;&gt;W&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-21825W\"></sup> us from it, and he will deliver<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-21825X&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference X&quot;&gt;X&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-21825X\"></sup> us from Your Majesty’s hand.",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>But even if he does not, we want you to know, Your Majesty, that we will not serve your gods or worship the image of gold you have set up.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-21826Y&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Y&quot;&gt;Y&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-21826Y\"></sup>”",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>Then Nebuchadnezzar was furious with Shadrach, Meshach and Abednego, and his attitude toward them changed. He ordered the furnace heated seven<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-21827Z&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Z&quot;&gt;Z&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-21827Z\"></sup> times hotter than usual",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup>and commanded some of the strongest soldiers in his army to tie up Shadrach, Meshach and Abednego<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-21828AA&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AA&quot;&gt;AA&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-21828AA\"></sup> and throw them into the blazing furnace.",
			"21": "<sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup>So these men, wearing their robes, trousers, turbans and other clothes, were bound and thrown into the blazing furnace.",
			"22": "<sup class=\"versenum\">22 </sup>The king’s command was so urgent and the furnace so hot that the flames of the fire killed the soldiers who took up Shadrach, Meshach and Abednego,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-21830AB&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AB&quot;&gt;AB&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-21830AB\"></sup>",
			"23": "<sup class=\"versenum\">23 </sup>and these three men, firmly tied, fell into the blazing furnace.",
			"24": "<sup class=\"versenum\">24 </sup>Then King Nebuchadnezzar leaped to his feet in amazement and asked his advisers, “Weren’t there three men that we tied up and threw into the fire?”They replied, “Certainly, Your Majesty.”",
			"25": "<sup class=\"versenum\">25 </sup>He said, “Look! I see four men walking around in the fire, unbound and unharmed, and the fourth looks like a son of the gods.”",
			"26": "<sup class=\"versenum\">26 </sup>Nebuchadnezzar then approached the opening of the blazing furnace and shouted, “Shadrach, Meshach and Abednego, servants of the Most High God,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-21834AC&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AC&quot;&gt;AC&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-21834AC\"></sup> come out! Come here!”So Shadrach, Meshach and Abednego came out of the fire,",
			"27": "<sup class=\"versenum\">27 </sup>and the satraps, prefects, governors and royal advisers<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-21835AD&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AD&quot;&gt;AD&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-21835AD\"></sup> crowded around them.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-21835AE&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AE&quot;&gt;AE&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-21835AE\"></sup> They saw that the fire<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-21835AF&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AF&quot;&gt;AF&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-21835AF\"></sup> had not harmed their bodies, nor was a hair of their heads singed; their robes were not scorched, and there was no smell of fire on them.",
			"28": "<sup class=\"versenum\">28 </sup>Then Nebuchadnezzar said, “Praise be to the God of Shadrach, Meshach and Abednego, who has sent his angel<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-21836AG&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AG&quot;&gt;AG&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-21836AG\"></sup> and rescued<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-21836AH&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AH&quot;&gt;AH&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-21836AH\"></sup> his servants! They trusted<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-21836AI&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AI&quot;&gt;AI&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-21836AI\"></sup> in him and defied the king’s command and were willing to give up their lives rather than serve or worship any god except their own God.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-21836AJ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AJ&quot;&gt;AJ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-21836AJ\"></sup>",
			"29": "<sup class=\"versenum\">29 </sup>Therefore I decree<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-21837AK&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AK&quot;&gt;AK&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-21837AK\"></sup> that the people of any nation or language who say anything against the God of Shadrach, Meshach and Abednego be cut into pieces and their houses be turned into piles of rubble,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-21837AL&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AL&quot;&gt;AL&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-21837AL\"></sup> for no other god can save<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-21837AM&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AM&quot;&gt;AM&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-21837AM\"></sup> in this way.”",
			"30": "<sup class=\"versenum\">30 </sup>Then the king promoted Shadrach, Meshach and Abednego in the province of Babylon.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-21838AN&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AN&quot;&gt;AN&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-21838AN\"></sup>"
		},
		"4": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">4 </span>King Nebuchadnezzar,To the nations and peoples of every language,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-21839A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-21839A\"></sup> who live in all the earth:May you prosper greatly!<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-21839B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-21839B\"></sup>",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>It is my pleasure to tell you about the miraculous signs<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-21840C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-21840C\"></sup> and wonders that the Most High God<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-21840D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-21840D\"></sup> has performed for me.",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>How great are his signs,how mighty his wonders!<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-21841E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-21841E\"></sup>His kingdom is an eternal kingdom;his dominion endures<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-21841F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-21841F\"></sup> from generation to generation.",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>I, Nebuchadnezzar, was at home in my palace, contented<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-21842G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-21842G\"></sup> and prosperous.",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>I had a dream<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-21843H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-21843H\"></sup> that made me afraid. As I was lying in bed,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-21843I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-21843I\"></sup> the images and visions that passed through my mind<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-21843J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-21843J\"></sup> terrified me.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-21843K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-21843K\"></sup>",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>So I commanded that all the wise men of Babylon be brought before me to interpret<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-21844L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-21844L\"></sup> the dream for me.",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>When the magicians,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-21845M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-21845M\"></sup> enchanters, astrologers and diviners<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-21845N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-21845N\"></sup> came, I told them the dream, but they could not interpret it for me.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-21845O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-21845O\"></sup>",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>Finally, Daniel came into my presence and I told him the dream. (He is called Belteshazzar,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-21846P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-21846P\"></sup> after the name of my god, and the spirit of the holy gods<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-21846Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-21846Q\"></sup> is in him.)",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>I said, “Belteshazzar, chief<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-21847R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-21847R\"></sup> of the magicians, I know that the spirit of the holy gods<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-21847S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-21847S\"></sup> is in you, and no mystery is too difficult for you. Here is my dream; interpret it for me.",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>These are the visions I saw while lying in bed:<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-21848T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-21848T\"></sup> I looked, and there before me stood a tree in the middle of the land. Its height was enormous.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-21848U&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference U&quot;&gt;U&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-21848U\"></sup>",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>The tree grew large and strong and its top touched the sky; it was visible to the ends of the earth.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-21849V&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference V&quot;&gt;V&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-21849V\"></sup>",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>Its leaves were beautiful, its fruit abundant, and on it was food for all. Under it the wild animals found shelter, and the birds lived in its branches;<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-21850W&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference W&quot;&gt;W&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-21850W\"></sup> from it every creature was fed.",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>“In the visions I saw while lying in bed,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-21851X&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference X&quot;&gt;X&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-21851X\"></sup> I looked, and there before me was a holy one,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-21851Y&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Y&quot;&gt;Y&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-21851Y\"></sup> a messenger, coming down from heaven.",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>He called in a loud voice: ‘Cut down the tree<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-21852Z&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Z&quot;&gt;Z&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-21852Z\"></sup> and trim off its branches; strip off its leaves and scatter its fruit. Let the animals flee from under it and the birds from its branches.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-21852AA&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AA&quot;&gt;AA&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-21852AA\"></sup>",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>But let the stump and its roots, bound with iron and bronze, remain in the ground, in the grass of the field.“‘Let him be drenched with the dew of heaven, and let him live with the animals among the plants of the earth.",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>Let his mind be changed from that of a man and let him be given the mind of an animal, till seven times pass by for him.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-21854AB&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AB&quot;&gt;AB&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-21854AB\"></sup>",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>“‘The decision is announced by messengers, the holy ones declare the verdict, so that the living may know that the Most High<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-21855AC&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AC&quot;&gt;AC&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-21855AC\"></sup> is sovereign<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-21855AD&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AD&quot;&gt;AD&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-21855AD\"></sup> over all kingdoms on earth and gives them to anyone he wishes and sets over them the lowliest<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-21855AE&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AE&quot;&gt;AE&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-21855AE\"></sup> of people.’",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>“This is the dream that I, King Nebuchadnezzar, had. Now, Belteshazzar, tell me what it means, for none of the wise men in my kingdom can interpret it for me.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-21856AF&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AF&quot;&gt;AF&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-21856AF\"></sup> But you can,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-21856AG&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AG&quot;&gt;AG&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-21856AG\"></sup> because the spirit of the holy gods<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-21856AH&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AH&quot;&gt;AH&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-21856AH\"></sup> is in you.”<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-21856AI&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AI&quot;&gt;AI&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-21856AI\"></sup>",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>Then Daniel (also called Belteshazzar) was greatly perplexed for a time, and his thoughts terrified<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-21857AJ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AJ&quot;&gt;AJ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-21857AJ\"></sup> him. So the king said, “Belteshazzar, do not let the dream or its meaning alarm you.”<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-21857AK&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AK&quot;&gt;AK&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-21857AK\"></sup>Belteshazzar answered, “My lord, if only the dream applied to your enemies and its meaning to your adversaries!",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup>The tree you saw, which grew large and strong, with its top touching the sky, visible to the whole earth,",
			"21": "<sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup>with beautiful leaves and abundant fruit, providing food for all, giving shelter to the wild animals, and having nesting places in its branches for the birds<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-21859AL&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AL&quot;&gt;AL&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-21859AL\"></sup>—",
			"22": "<sup class=\"versenum\">22 </sup>Your Majesty, you are that tree!<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-21860AM&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AM&quot;&gt;AM&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-21860AM\"></sup> You have become great and strong; your greatness has grown until it reaches the sky, and your dominion extends to distant parts of the earth.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-21860AN&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AN&quot;&gt;AN&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-21860AN\"></sup>",
			"23": "<sup class=\"versenum\">23 </sup>“Your Majesty saw a holy one,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-21861AO&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AO&quot;&gt;AO&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-21861AO\"></sup> a messenger, coming down from heaven and saying, ‘Cut down the tree and destroy it, but leave the stump, bound with iron and bronze, in the grass of the field, while its roots remain in the ground. Let him be drenched with the dew of heaven; let him live with the wild animals, until seven times pass by for him.’<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-21861AP&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AP&quot;&gt;AP&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-21861AP\"></sup>",
			"24": "<sup class=\"versenum\">24 </sup>“This is the interpretation, Your Majesty, and this is the decree<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-21862AQ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AQ&quot;&gt;AQ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-21862AQ\"></sup> the Most High has issued against my lord the king:",
			"25": "<sup class=\"versenum\">25 </sup>You will be driven away from people and will live with the wild animals; you will eat grass like the ox and be drenched<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-21863AR&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AR&quot;&gt;AR&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-21863AR\"></sup> with the dew of heaven. Seven times will pass by for you until you acknowledge that the Most High<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-21863AS&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AS&quot;&gt;AS&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-21863AS\"></sup> is sovereign over all kingdoms on earth and gives them to anyone he wishes.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-21863AT&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AT&quot;&gt;AT&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-21863AT\"></sup>",
			"26": "<sup class=\"versenum\">26 </sup>The command to leave the stump of the tree with its roots<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-21864AU&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AU&quot;&gt;AU&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-21864AU\"></sup> means that your kingdom will be restored to you when you acknowledge that Heaven rules.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-21864AV&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AV&quot;&gt;AV&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-21864AV\"></sup>",
			"27": "<sup class=\"versenum\">27 </sup>Therefore, Your Majesty, be pleased to accept my advice: Renounce your sins by doing what is right, and your wickedness by being kind to the oppressed.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-21865AW&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AW&quot;&gt;AW&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-21865AW\"></sup> It may be that then your prosperity<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-21865AX&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AX&quot;&gt;AX&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-21865AX\"></sup> will continue.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-21865AY&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AY&quot;&gt;AY&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-21865AY\"></sup>”",
			"28": "<sup class=\"versenum\">28 </sup>All this happened<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-21866AZ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AZ&quot;&gt;AZ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-21866AZ\"></sup> to King Nebuchadnezzar.",
			"29": "<sup class=\"versenum\">29 </sup>Twelve months later, as the king was walking on the roof of the royal palace of Babylon,",
			"30": "<sup class=\"versenum\">30 </sup>he said, “Is not this the great Babylon I have built as the royal residence, by my mighty power and for the glory<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-21868BA&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BA&quot;&gt;BA&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-21868BA\"></sup> of my majesty?”<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-21868BB&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BB&quot;&gt;BB&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-21868BB\"></sup>",
			"31": "<sup class=\"versenum\">31 </sup>Even as the words were on his lips, a voice came from heaven, “This is what is decreed for you, King Nebuchadnezzar: Your royal authority has been taken from you.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-21869BC&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BC&quot;&gt;BC&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-21869BC\"></sup>",
			"32": "<sup class=\"versenum\">32 </sup>You will be driven away from people and will live with the wild animals; you will eat grass like the ox. Seven times will pass by for you until you acknowledge that the Most High is sovereign over all kingdoms on earth and gives them to anyone he wishes.”<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-21870BD&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BD&quot;&gt;BD&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-21870BD\"></sup>",
			"33": "<sup class=\"versenum\">33 </sup>Immediately what had been said about Nebuchadnezzar was fulfilled. He was driven away from people and ate grass like the ox. His body was drenched<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-21871BE&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BE&quot;&gt;BE&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-21871BE\"></sup> with the dew of heaven until his hair grew like the feathers of an eagle and his nails like the claws of a bird.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-21871BF&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BF&quot;&gt;BF&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-21871BF\"></sup>",
			"34": "<sup class=\"versenum\">34 </sup>At the end of that time, I, Nebuchadnezzar, raised my eyes toward heaven, and my sanity<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-21872BG&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BG&quot;&gt;BG&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-21872BG\"></sup> was restored. Then I praised the Most High; I honored and glorified him who lives forever.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-21872BH&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BH&quot;&gt;BH&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-21872BH\"></sup>His dominion is an eternal dominion;his kingdom<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-21872BI&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BI&quot;&gt;BI&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-21872BI\"></sup> endures from generation to generation.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-21872BJ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BJ&quot;&gt;BJ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-21872BJ\"></sup>",
			"35": "<sup class=\"versenum\">35 </sup>All the peoples of the earthare regarded as nothing.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-21873BK&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BK&quot;&gt;BK&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-21873BK\"></sup>He does as he pleases<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-21873BL&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BL&quot;&gt;BL&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-21873BL\"></sup>with the powers of heavenand the peoples of the earth.No one can hold back<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-21873BM&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BM&quot;&gt;BM&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-21873BM\"></sup> his hand<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-21873BN&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BN&quot;&gt;BN&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-21873BN\"></sup>or say to him: “What have you done?”<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-21873BO&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BO&quot;&gt;BO&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-21873BO\"></sup>",
			"36": "<sup class=\"versenum\">36 </sup>At the same time that my sanity was restored, my honor and splendor were returned to me for the glory of my kingdom.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-21874BP&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BP&quot;&gt;BP&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-21874BP\"></sup> My advisers and nobles sought me out, and I was restored to my throne and became even greater than before.",
			"37": "<sup class=\"versenum\">37 </sup>Now I, Nebuchadnezzar, praise and exalt<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-21875BQ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BQ&quot;&gt;BQ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-21875BQ\"></sup> and glorify<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-21875BR&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BR&quot;&gt;BR&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-21875BR\"></sup> the King of heaven, because everything he does is right and all his ways are just.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-21875BS&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BS&quot;&gt;BS&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-21875BS\"></sup> And those who walk in pride<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-21875BT&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BT&quot;&gt;BT&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-21875BT\"></sup> he is able to humble.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-21875BU&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BU&quot;&gt;BU&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-21875BU\"></sup>"
		},
		"5": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">5 </span>King Belshazzar<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-21876A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-21876A\"></sup> gave a great banquet<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-21876B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-21876B\"></sup> for a thousand of his nobles<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-21876C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-21876C\"></sup> and drank wine with them.",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>While Belshazzar was drinking<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-21877D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-21877D\"></sup> his wine, he gave orders to bring in the gold and silver goblets<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-21877E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-21877E\"></sup> that Nebuchadnezzar his father had taken from the temple in Jerusalem, so that the king and his nobles, his wives and his concubines<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-21877F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-21877F\"></sup> might drink from them.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-21877G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-21877G\"></sup>",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>So they brought in the gold goblets that had been taken from the temple of God in Jerusalem, and the king and his nobles, his wives and his concubines drank from them.",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>As they drank the wine, they praised the gods<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-21879H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-21879H\"></sup> of gold and silver, of bronze, iron, wood and stone.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-21879I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-21879I\"></sup>",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>Suddenly the fingers of a human hand appeared and wrote on the plaster of the wall, near the lampstand in the royal palace. The king watched the hand as it wrote.",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>His face turned pale<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-21881J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-21881J\"></sup> and he was so frightened<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-21881K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-21881K\"></sup> that his legs became weak<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-21881L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-21881L\"></sup> and his knees were knocking.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-21881M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-21881M\"></sup>",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>The king summoned the enchanters,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-21882N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-21882N\"></sup> astrologers<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-21882O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-21882O\"></sup> and diviners.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-21882P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-21882P\"></sup> Then he said to these wise<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-21882Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-21882Q\"></sup> men of Babylon, “Whoever reads this writing and tells me what it means will be clothed in purple and have a gold chain placed around his neck,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-21882R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-21882R\"></sup> and he will be made the third<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-21882S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-21882S\"></sup> highest ruler in the kingdom.”<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-21882T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-21882T\"></sup>",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>Then all the king’s wise men<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-21883U&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference U&quot;&gt;U&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-21883U\"></sup> came in, but they could not read the writing or tell the king what it meant.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-21883V&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference V&quot;&gt;V&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-21883V\"></sup>",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>So King Belshazzar became even more terrified<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-21884W&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference W&quot;&gt;W&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-21884W\"></sup> and his face grew more pale. His nobles were baffled.",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>The queen, hearing the voices of the king and his nobles, came into the banquet hall. “May the king live forever!”<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-21885X&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference X&quot;&gt;X&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-21885X\"></sup> she said. “Don’t be alarmed! Don’t look so pale!",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>There is a man in your kingdom who has the spirit of the holy gods<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-21886Y&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Y&quot;&gt;Y&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-21886Y\"></sup> in him. In the time of your father he was found to have insight and intelligence and wisdom<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-21886Z&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Z&quot;&gt;Z&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-21886Z\"></sup> like that of the gods.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-21886AA&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AA&quot;&gt;AA&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-21886AA\"></sup> Your father, King Nebuchadnezzar, appointed him chief of the magicians, enchanters, astrologers and diviners.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-21886AB&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AB&quot;&gt;AB&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-21886AB\"></sup>",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>He did this because Daniel, whom the king called Belteshazzar,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-21887AC&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AC&quot;&gt;AC&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-21887AC\"></sup> was found to have a keen mind and knowledge and understanding, and also the ability to interpret dreams, explain riddles<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-21887AD&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AD&quot;&gt;AD&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-21887AD\"></sup> and solve difficult problems.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-21887AE&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AE&quot;&gt;AE&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-21887AE\"></sup> Call for Daniel, and he will tell you what the writing means.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-21887AF&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AF&quot;&gt;AF&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-21887AF\"></sup>”",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>So Daniel was brought before the king, and the king said to him, “Are you Daniel, one of the exiles my father the king brought from Judah?<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-21888AG&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AG&quot;&gt;AG&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-21888AG\"></sup>",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>I have heard that the spirit of the gods<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-21889AH&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AH&quot;&gt;AH&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-21889AH\"></sup> is in you and that you have insight, intelligence and outstanding wisdom.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-21889AI&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AI&quot;&gt;AI&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-21889AI\"></sup>",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>The wise men and enchanters were brought before me to read this writing and tell me what it means, but they could not explain it.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-21890AJ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AJ&quot;&gt;AJ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-21890AJ\"></sup>",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>Now I have heard that you are able to give interpretations and to solve difficult problems.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-21891AK&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AK&quot;&gt;AK&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-21891AK\"></sup> If you can read this writing and tell me what it means, you will be clothed in purple and have a gold chain placed around your neck,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-21891AL&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AL&quot;&gt;AL&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-21891AL\"></sup> and you will be made the third highest ruler in the kingdom.”<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-21891AM&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AM&quot;&gt;AM&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-21891AM\"></sup>",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>Then Daniel answered the king, “You may keep your gifts for yourself and give your rewards to someone else.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-21892AN&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AN&quot;&gt;AN&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-21892AN\"></sup> Nevertheless, I will read the writing for the king and tell him what it means.",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>“Your Majesty, the Most High God gave your father Nebuchadnezzar<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-21893AO&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AO&quot;&gt;AO&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-21893AO\"></sup> sovereignty and greatness and glory and splendor.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-21893AP&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AP&quot;&gt;AP&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-21893AP\"></sup>",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>Because of the high position he gave him, all the nations and peoples of every language dreaded and feared him. Those the king wanted to put to death, he put to death;<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-21894AQ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AQ&quot;&gt;AQ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-21894AQ\"></sup> those he wanted to spare, he spared; those he wanted to promote, he promoted; and those he wanted to humble, he humbled.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-21894AR&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AR&quot;&gt;AR&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-21894AR\"></sup>",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup>But when his heart became arrogant and hardened with pride,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-21895AS&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AS&quot;&gt;AS&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-21895AS\"></sup> he was deposed from his royal throne<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-21895AT&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AT&quot;&gt;AT&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-21895AT\"></sup> and stripped<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-21895AU&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AU&quot;&gt;AU&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-21895AU\"></sup> of his glory.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-21895AV&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AV&quot;&gt;AV&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-21895AV\"></sup>",
			"21": "<sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup>He was driven away from people and given the mind of an animal; he lived with the wild donkeys and ate grass like the ox; and his body was drenched with the dew of heaven, until he acknowledged that the Most High God is sovereign<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-21896AW&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AW&quot;&gt;AW&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-21896AW\"></sup> over all kingdoms on earth and sets over them anyone he wishes.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-21896AX&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AX&quot;&gt;AX&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-21896AX\"></sup>",
			"22": "<sup class=\"versenum\">22 </sup>“But you, Belshazzar, his son, have not humbled<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-21897AY&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AY&quot;&gt;AY&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-21897AY\"></sup> yourself, though you knew all this.",
			"23": "<sup class=\"versenum\">23 </sup>Instead, you have set yourself up against<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-21898AZ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AZ&quot;&gt;AZ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-21898AZ\"></sup> the Lord of heaven. You had the goblets from his temple brought to you, and you and your nobles, your wives<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-21898BA&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BA&quot;&gt;BA&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-21898BA\"></sup> and your concubines drank wine from them. You praised the gods of silver and gold, of bronze, iron, wood and stone, which cannot see or hear or understand.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-21898BB&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BB&quot;&gt;BB&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-21898BB\"></sup> But you did not honor the God who holds in his hand your life<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-21898BC&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BC&quot;&gt;BC&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-21898BC\"></sup> and all your ways.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-21898BD&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BD&quot;&gt;BD&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-21898BD\"></sup>",
			"24": "<sup class=\"versenum\">24 </sup>Therefore he sent the hand that wrote the inscription.",
			"25": "<sup class=\"versenum\">25 </sup>“This is the inscription that was written:<span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">mene, mene, tekel, parsin</span>",
			"26": "<sup class=\"versenum\">26 </sup>“Here is what these words mean:<i>Mene</i>: God has numbered the days<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-21901BE&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BE&quot;&gt;BE&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-21901BE\"></sup> of your reign and brought it to an end.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-21901BF&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BF&quot;&gt;BF&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-21901BF\"></sup>",
			"27": "<sup class=\"versenum\">27 </sup><i>Tekel</i>: You have been weighed on the scales<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-21902BG&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BG&quot;&gt;BG&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-21902BG\"></sup> and found wanting.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-21902BH&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BH&quot;&gt;BH&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-21902BH\"></sup>",
			"28": "<sup class=\"versenum\">28 </sup><i>Peres</i>: Your kingdom is divided and given to the Medes<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-21903BI&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BI&quot;&gt;BI&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-21903BI\"></sup> and Persians.”<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-21903BJ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BJ&quot;&gt;BJ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-21903BJ\"></sup>",
			"29": "<sup class=\"versenum\">29 </sup>Then at Belshazzar’s command, Daniel was clothed in purple, a gold chain was placed around his neck,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-21904BK&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BK&quot;&gt;BK&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-21904BK\"></sup> and he was proclaimed the third highest ruler in the kingdom.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-21904BL&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BL&quot;&gt;BL&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-21904BL\"></sup>",
			"30": "<sup class=\"versenum\">30 </sup>That very night Belshazzar,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-21905BM&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BM&quot;&gt;BM&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-21905BM\"></sup> king<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-21905BN&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BN&quot;&gt;BN&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-21905BN\"></sup> of the Babylonians, was slain,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-21905BO&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BO&quot;&gt;BO&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-21905BO\"></sup>",
			"31": "<sup class=\"versenum\">31 </sup>and Darius<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-21906BP&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BP&quot;&gt;BP&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-21906BP\"></sup> the Mede<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-21906BQ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BQ&quot;&gt;BQ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-21906BQ\"></sup> took over the kingdom, at the age of sixty-two."
		},
		"6": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">6 </span>It pleased Darius<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-21907A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-21907A\"></sup> to appoint 120 satraps<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-21907B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-21907B\"></sup> to rule throughout the kingdom,",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>with three administrators over them, one of whom was Daniel.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-21908C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-21908C\"></sup> The satraps were made accountable<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-21908D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-21908D\"></sup> to them so that the king might not suffer loss.",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>Now Daniel so distinguished himself among the administrators and the satraps by his exceptional qualities that the king planned to set him over the whole kingdom.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-21909E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-21909E\"></sup>",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>At this, the administrators and the satraps tried to find grounds for charges<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-21910F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-21910F\"></sup> against Daniel in his conduct of government affairs, but they were unable to do so. They could find no corruption in him, because he was trustworthy and neither corrupt nor negligent.",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>Finally these men said, “We will never find any basis for charges against this man Daniel unless it has something to do with the law of his God.”<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-21911G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-21911G\"></sup>",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>So these administrators and satraps went as a group to the king and said: “May King Darius live forever!<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-21912H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-21912H\"></sup>",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>The royal administrators, prefects, satraps, advisers and governors<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-21913I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-21913I\"></sup> have all agreed that the king should issue an edict and enforce the decree that anyone who prays to any god or human being during the next thirty days, except to you, Your Majesty, shall be thrown into the lions’ den.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-21913J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-21913J\"></sup>",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>Now, Your Majesty, issue the decree and put it in writing so that it cannot be altered—in accordance with the law of the Medes and Persians, which cannot be repealed.”<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-21914K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-21914K\"></sup>",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>So King Darius put the decree in writing.",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>Now when Daniel learned that the decree had been published, he went home to his upstairs room where the windows opened toward<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-21916L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-21916L\"></sup> Jerusalem. Three times a day he got down on his knees<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-21916M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-21916M\"></sup> and prayed, giving thanks to his God, just as he had done before.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-21916N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-21916N\"></sup>",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>Then these men went as a group and found Daniel praying and asking God for help.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-21917O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-21917O\"></sup>",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>So they went to the king and spoke to him about his royal decree: “Did you not publish a decree that during the next thirty days anyone who prays to any god or human being except to you, Your Majesty, would be thrown into the lions’ den?”The king answered, “The decree stands—in accordance with the law of the Medes and Persians, which cannot be repealed.”<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-21918P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-21918P\"></sup>",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>Then they said to the king, “Daniel, who is one of the exiles from Judah,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-21919Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-21919Q\"></sup> pays no attention<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-21919R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-21919R\"></sup> to you, Your Majesty, or to the decree you put in writing. He still prays three times a day.”",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>When the king heard this, he was greatly distressed;<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-21920S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-21920S\"></sup> he was determined to rescue Daniel and made every effort until sundown to save him.",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>Then the men went as a group to King Darius and said to him, “Remember, Your Majesty, that according to the law of the Medes and Persians no decree or edict that the king issues can be changed.”<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-21921T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-21921T\"></sup>",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>So the king gave the order, and they brought Daniel and threw him into the lions’ den.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-21922U&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference U&quot;&gt;U&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-21922U\"></sup> The king said to Daniel, “May your God, whom you serve continually, rescue<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-21922V&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference V&quot;&gt;V&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-21922V\"></sup> you!”",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>A stone was brought and placed over the mouth of the den, and the king sealed<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-21923W&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference W&quot;&gt;W&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-21923W\"></sup> it with his own signet ring and with the rings of his nobles, so that Daniel’s situation might not be changed.",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>Then the king returned to his palace and spent the night without eating<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-21924X&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference X&quot;&gt;X&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-21924X\"></sup> and without any entertainment being brought to him. And he could not sleep.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-21924Y&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Y&quot;&gt;Y&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-21924Y\"></sup>",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>At the first light of dawn, the king got up and hurried to the lions’ den.",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup>When he came near the den, he called to Daniel in an anguished voice, “Daniel, servant of the living God, has your God, whom you serve continually, been able to rescue you from the lions?”<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-21926Z&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Z&quot;&gt;Z&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-21926Z\"></sup>",
			"21": "<sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup>Daniel answered, “May the king live forever!<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-21927AA&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AA&quot;&gt;AA&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-21927AA\"></sup>",
			"22": "<sup class=\"versenum\">22 </sup>My God sent his angel,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-21928AB&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AB&quot;&gt;AB&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-21928AB\"></sup> and he shut the mouths of the lions.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-21928AC&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AC&quot;&gt;AC&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-21928AC\"></sup> They have not hurt me, because I was found innocent in his sight.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-21928AD&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AD&quot;&gt;AD&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-21928AD\"></sup> Nor have I ever done any wrong before you, Your Majesty.”",
			"23": "<sup class=\"versenum\">23 </sup>The king was overjoyed and gave orders to lift Daniel out of the den. And when Daniel was lifted from the den, no wound<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-21929AE&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AE&quot;&gt;AE&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-21929AE\"></sup> was found on him, because he had trusted<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-21929AF&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AF&quot;&gt;AF&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-21929AF\"></sup> in his God.",
			"24": "<sup class=\"versenum\">24 </sup>At the king’s command, the men who had falsely accused Daniel were brought in and thrown into the lions’ den,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-21930AG&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AG&quot;&gt;AG&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-21930AG\"></sup> along with their wives and children.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-21930AH&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AH&quot;&gt;AH&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-21930AH\"></sup> And before they reached the floor of the den, the lions overpowered them and crushed all their bones.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-21930AI&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AI&quot;&gt;AI&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-21930AI\"></sup>",
			"25": "<sup class=\"versenum\">25 </sup>Then King Darius wrote to all the nations and peoples of every language<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-21931AJ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AJ&quot;&gt;AJ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-21931AJ\"></sup> in all the earth:“May you prosper greatly!<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-21931AK&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AK&quot;&gt;AK&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-21931AK\"></sup>",
			"26": "<sup class=\"versenum\">26 </sup>“I issue a decree that in every part of my kingdom people must fear and reverence<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-21932AL&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AL&quot;&gt;AL&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-21932AL\"></sup> the God of Daniel.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-21932AM&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AM&quot;&gt;AM&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-21932AM\"></sup>“For he is the living God<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-21932AN&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AN&quot;&gt;AN&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-21932AN\"></sup>and he endures forever;<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-21932AO&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AO&quot;&gt;AO&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-21932AO\"></sup>his kingdom will not be destroyed,his dominion will never end.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-21932AP&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AP&quot;&gt;AP&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-21932AP\"></sup>",
			"27": "<sup class=\"versenum\">27 </sup>He rescues and he saves;<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-21933AQ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AQ&quot;&gt;AQ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-21933AQ\"></sup>he performs signs and wonders<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-21933AR&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AR&quot;&gt;AR&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-21933AR\"></sup>in the heavens and on the earth.He has rescued Danielfrom the power of the lions.”<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-21933AS&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AS&quot;&gt;AS&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-21933AS\"></sup>",
			"28": "<sup class=\"versenum\">28 </sup>So Daniel prospered during the reign of Darius and the reign of Cyrus<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-21934AT&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AT&quot;&gt;AT&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-21934AT\"></sup> the Persian.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-21934AU&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AU&quot;&gt;AU&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-21934AU\"></sup>"
		},
		"7": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">7 </span>In the first year of Belshazzar<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-21935A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-21935A\"></sup> king of Babylon, Daniel had a dream, and visions<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-21935B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-21935B\"></sup> passed through his mind<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-21935C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-21935C\"></sup> as he was lying in bed.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-21935D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-21935D\"></sup> He wrote<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-21935E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-21935E\"></sup> down the substance of his dream.",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>Daniel said: “In my vision at night I looked, and there before me were the four winds of heaven<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-21936F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-21936F\"></sup> churning up the great sea.",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>Four great beasts,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-21937G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-21937G\"></sup> each different from the others, came up out of the sea.",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>“The first was like a lion,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-21938H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-21938H\"></sup> and it had the wings of an eagle.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-21938I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-21938I\"></sup> I watched until its wings were torn off and it was lifted from the ground so that it stood on two feet like a human being, and the mind of a human was given to it.",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>“And there before me was a second beast, which looked like a bear. It was raised up on one of its sides, and it had three ribs in its mouth between its teeth. It was told, ‘Get up and eat your fill of flesh!’<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-21939J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-21939J\"></sup>",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>“After that, I looked, and there before me was another beast, one that looked like a leopard.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-21940K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-21940K\"></sup> And on its back it had four wings like those of a bird. This beast had four heads, and it was given authority to rule.",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>“After that, in my vision<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-21941L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-21941L\"></sup> at night I looked, and there before me was a fourth beast—terrifying and frightening and very powerful. It had large iron<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-21941M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-21941M\"></sup> teeth; it crushed and devoured its victims and trampled<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-21941N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-21941N\"></sup> underfoot whatever was left.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-21941O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-21941O\"></sup> It was different from all the former beasts, and it had ten horns.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-21941P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-21941P\"></sup>",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>“While I was thinking about the horns, there before me was another horn, a little<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-21942Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-21942Q\"></sup> one, which came up among them; and three of the first horns were uprooted before it. This horn had eyes like the eyes of a human being<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-21942R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-21942R\"></sup> and a mouth that spoke boastfully.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-21942S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-21942S\"></sup>",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>“As I looked,“thrones were set in place,and the Ancient of Days<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-21943T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-21943T\"></sup> took his seat.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-21943U&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference U&quot;&gt;U&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-21943U\"></sup>His clothing was as white as snow;<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-21943V&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference V&quot;&gt;V&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-21943V\"></sup>the hair of his head was white like wool.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-21943W&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference W&quot;&gt;W&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-21943W\"></sup>His throne was flaming with fire,and its wheels<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-21943X&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference X&quot;&gt;X&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-21943X\"></sup> were all ablaze.",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>A river of fire<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-21944Y&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Y&quot;&gt;Y&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-21944Y\"></sup> was flowing,coming out from before him.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-21944Z&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Z&quot;&gt;Z&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-21944Z\"></sup>Thousands upon thousands attended him;ten thousand times ten thousand stood before him.The court was seated,and the books<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-21944AA&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AA&quot;&gt;AA&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-21944AA\"></sup> were opened.",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>“Then I continued to watch because of the boastful words the horn was speaking.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-21945AB&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AB&quot;&gt;AB&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-21945AB\"></sup> I kept looking until the beast was slain and its body destroyed and thrown into the blazing fire.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-21945AC&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AC&quot;&gt;AC&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-21945AC\"></sup>",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>(The other beasts had been stripped of their authority, but were allowed to live for a period of time.)",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>“In my vision at night I looked, and there before me was one like a son of man,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-21947AD&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AD&quot;&gt;AD&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-21947AD\"></sup> coming<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-21947AE&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AE&quot;&gt;AE&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-21947AE\"></sup> with the clouds of heaven.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-21947AF&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AF&quot;&gt;AF&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-21947AF\"></sup> He approached the Ancient of Days and was led into his presence.",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>He was given authority,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-21948AG&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AG&quot;&gt;AG&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-21948AG\"></sup> glory and sovereign power; all nations and peoples of every language worshiped him.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-21948AH&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AH&quot;&gt;AH&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-21948AH\"></sup> His dominion is an everlasting dominion that will not pass away, and his kingdom<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-21948AI&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AI&quot;&gt;AI&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-21948AI\"></sup> is one that will never be destroyed.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-21948AJ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AJ&quot;&gt;AJ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-21948AJ\"></sup>",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>“I, Daniel, was troubled in spirit, and the visions that passed through my mind disturbed me.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-21949AK&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AK&quot;&gt;AK&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-21949AK\"></sup>",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>I approached one of those standing there and asked him the meaning of all this.“So he told me and gave me the interpretation<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-21950AL&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AL&quot;&gt;AL&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-21950AL\"></sup> of these things:",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>‘The four great beasts are four kings that will rise from the earth.",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>But the holy people<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-21952AM&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AM&quot;&gt;AM&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-21952AM\"></sup> of the Most High will receive the kingdom<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-21952AN&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AN&quot;&gt;AN&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-21952AN\"></sup> and will possess it forever—yes, for ever and ever.’<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-21952AO&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AO&quot;&gt;AO&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-21952AO\"></sup>",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>“Then I wanted to know the meaning of the fourth beast, which was different from all the others and most terrifying, with its iron teeth and bronze claws—the beast that crushed and devoured its victims and trampled underfoot whatever was left.",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup>I also wanted to know about the ten horns<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-21954AP&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AP&quot;&gt;AP&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-21954AP\"></sup> on its head and about the other horn that came up, before which three of them fell—the horn that looked more imposing than the others and that had eyes and a mouth that spoke boastfully.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-21954AQ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AQ&quot;&gt;AQ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-21954AQ\"></sup>",
			"21": "<sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup>As I watched, this horn was waging war against the holy people and defeating them,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-21955AR&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AR&quot;&gt;AR&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-21955AR\"></sup>",
			"22": "<sup class=\"versenum\">22 </sup>until the Ancient of Days came and pronounced judgment in favor of the holy people of the Most High, and the time came when they possessed the kingdom.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-21956AS&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AS&quot;&gt;AS&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-21956AS\"></sup>",
			"23": "<sup class=\"versenum\">23 </sup>“He gave me this explanation: ‘The fourth beast is a fourth kingdom that will appear on earth. It will be different from all the other kingdoms and will devour the whole earth, trampling it down and crushing it.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-21957AT&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AT&quot;&gt;AT&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-21957AT\"></sup>",
			"24": "<sup class=\"versenum\">24 </sup>The ten horns<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-21958AU&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AU&quot;&gt;AU&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-21958AU\"></sup> are ten kings who will come from this kingdom. After them another king will arise, different from the earlier ones; he will subdue three kings.",
			"25": "<sup class=\"versenum\">25 </sup>He will speak against the Most High<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-21959AV&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AV&quot;&gt;AV&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-21959AV\"></sup> and oppress his holy people<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-21959AW&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AW&quot;&gt;AW&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-21959AW\"></sup> and try to change the set times<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-21959AX&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AX&quot;&gt;AX&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-21959AX\"></sup> and the laws. The holy people will be delivered into his hands for a time, times and half a time.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-21959AY&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AY&quot;&gt;AY&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-21959AY\"></sup>",
			"26": "<sup class=\"versenum\">26 </sup>“‘But the court will sit, and his power will be taken away and completely destroyed<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-21960AZ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AZ&quot;&gt;AZ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-21960AZ\"></sup> forever.",
			"27": "<sup class=\"versenum\">27 </sup>Then the sovereignty, power and greatness of all the kingdoms<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-21961BA&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BA&quot;&gt;BA&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-21961BA\"></sup> under heaven will be handed over to the holy people<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-21961BB&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BB&quot;&gt;BB&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-21961BB\"></sup> of the Most High.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-21961BC&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BC&quot;&gt;BC&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-21961BC\"></sup> His kingdom will be an everlasting<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-21961BD&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BD&quot;&gt;BD&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-21961BD\"></sup> kingdom, and all rulers will worship<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-21961BE&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BE&quot;&gt;BE&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-21961BE\"></sup> and obey him.’",
			"28": "<sup class=\"versenum\">28 </sup>“This is the end of the matter. I, Daniel, was deeply troubled<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-21962BF&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BF&quot;&gt;BF&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-21962BF\"></sup> by my thoughts,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-21962BG&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BG&quot;&gt;BG&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-21962BG\"></sup> and my face turned pale,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-21962BH&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BH&quot;&gt;BH&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-21962BH\"></sup> but I kept the matter to myself.”"
		},
		"8": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">8 </span>In the third year of King Belshazzar’s<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-21963A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-21963A\"></sup> reign, I, Daniel, had a vision,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-21963B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-21963B\"></sup> after the one that had already appeared to me.",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>In my vision I saw myself in the citadel of Susa<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-21964C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-21964C\"></sup> in the province of Elam;<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-21964D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-21964D\"></sup> in the vision I was beside the Ulai Canal.",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>I looked up,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-21965E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-21965E\"></sup> and there before me was a ram<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-21965F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-21965F\"></sup> with two horns, standing beside the canal, and the horns were long. One of the horns was longer than the other but grew up later.",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>I watched the ram as it charged toward the west and the north and the south. No animal could stand against it, and none could rescue from its power.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-21966G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-21966G\"></sup> It did as it pleased<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-21966H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-21966H\"></sup> and became great.",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>As I was thinking about this, suddenly a goat with a prominent horn between its eyes came from the west, crossing the whole earth without touching the ground.",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>It came toward the two-horned ram I had seen standing beside the canal and charged at it in great rage.",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>I saw it attack the ram furiously, striking the ram and shattering its two horns. The ram was powerless to stand against it; the goat knocked it to the ground and trampled on it,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-21969I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-21969I\"></sup> and none could rescue the ram from its power.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-21969J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-21969J\"></sup>",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>The goat became very great, but at the height of its power the large horn was broken off,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-21970K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-21970K\"></sup> and in its place four prominent horns grew up toward the four winds of heaven.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-21970L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-21970L\"></sup>",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>Out of one of them came another horn, which started small<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-21971M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-21971M\"></sup> but grew in power to the south and to the east and toward the Beautiful Land.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-21971N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-21971N\"></sup>",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>It grew until it reached<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-21972O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-21972O\"></sup> the host of the heavens, and it threw some of the starry host down to the earth<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-21972P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-21972P\"></sup> and trampled<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-21972Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-21972Q\"></sup> on them.",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>It set itself up to be as great as the commander<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-21973R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-21973R\"></sup> of the army of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>;<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-21973S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-21973S\"></sup> it took away the daily sacrifice<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-21973T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-21973T\"></sup> from the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, and his sanctuary was thrown down.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-21973U&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference U&quot;&gt;U&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-21973U\"></sup>",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>Because of rebellion, the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>’s people and the daily sacrifice were given over to it. It prospered in everything it did, and truth was thrown to the ground.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-21974V&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference V&quot;&gt;V&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-21974V\"></sup>",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>Then I heard a holy one<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-21975W&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference W&quot;&gt;W&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-21975W\"></sup> speaking, and another holy one said to him, “How long will it take for the vision to be fulfilled<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-21975X&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference X&quot;&gt;X&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-21975X\"></sup>—the vision concerning the daily sacrifice, the rebellion that causes desolation, the surrender of the sanctuary and the trampling underfoot<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-21975Y&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Y&quot;&gt;Y&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-21975Y\"></sup> of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>’s people?”",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>He said to me, “It will take 2,300 evenings and mornings; then the sanctuary will be reconsecrated.”<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-21976Z&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Z&quot;&gt;Z&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-21976Z\"></sup>",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>While I, Daniel, was watching the vision<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-21977AA&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AA&quot;&gt;AA&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-21977AA\"></sup> and trying to understand it, there before me stood one who looked like a man.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-21977AB&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AB&quot;&gt;AB&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-21977AB\"></sup>",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>And I heard a man’s voice from the Ulai<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-21978AC&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AC&quot;&gt;AC&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-21978AC\"></sup> calling, “Gabriel,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-21978AD&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AD&quot;&gt;AD&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-21978AD\"></sup> tell this man the meaning of the vision.”<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-21978AE&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AE&quot;&gt;AE&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-21978AE\"></sup>",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>As he came near the place where I was standing, I was terrified and fell prostrate.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-21979AF&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AF&quot;&gt;AF&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-21979AF\"></sup> “Son of man,” he said to me, “understand that the vision concerns the time of the end.”<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-21979AG&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AG&quot;&gt;AG&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-21979AG\"></sup>",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>While he was speaking to me, I was in a deep sleep, with my face to the ground.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-21980AH&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AH&quot;&gt;AH&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-21980AH\"></sup> Then he touched me and raised me to my feet.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-21980AI&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AI&quot;&gt;AI&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-21980AI\"></sup>",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>He said: “I am going to tell you what will happen later in the time of wrath,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-21981AJ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AJ&quot;&gt;AJ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-21981AJ\"></sup> because the vision concerns the appointed time<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-21981AK&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AK&quot;&gt;AK&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-21981AK\"></sup> of the end.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-21981AL&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AL&quot;&gt;AL&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-21981AL\"></sup>",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup>The two-horned ram that you saw represents the kings of Media and Persia.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-21982AM&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AM&quot;&gt;AM&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-21982AM\"></sup>",
			"21": "<sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup>The shaggy goat is the king of Greece,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-21983AN&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AN&quot;&gt;AN&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-21983AN\"></sup> and the large horn between its eyes is the first king.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-21983AO&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AO&quot;&gt;AO&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-21983AO\"></sup>",
			"22": "<sup class=\"versenum\">22 </sup>The four horns that replaced the one that was broken off represent four kingdoms that will emerge from his nation but will not have the same power.",
			"23": "<sup class=\"versenum\">23 </sup>“In the latter part of their reign, when rebels have become completely wicked, a fierce-looking king, a master of intrigue, will arise.",
			"24": "<sup class=\"versenum\">24 </sup>He will become very strong, but not by his own power. He will cause astounding devastation and will succeed in whatever he does. He will destroy those who are mighty, the holy people.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-21986AP&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AP&quot;&gt;AP&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-21986AP\"></sup>",
			"25": "<sup class=\"versenum\">25 </sup>He will cause deceit<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-21987AQ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AQ&quot;&gt;AQ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-21987AQ\"></sup> to prosper, and he will consider himself superior. When they feel secure, he will destroy many and take his stand against the Prince of princes.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-21987AR&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AR&quot;&gt;AR&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-21987AR\"></sup> Yet he will be destroyed, but not by human power.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-21987AS&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AS&quot;&gt;AS&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-21987AS\"></sup>",
			"26": "<sup class=\"versenum\">26 </sup>“The vision of the evenings and mornings that has been given you is true,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-21988AT&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AT&quot;&gt;AT&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-21988AT\"></sup> but seal<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-21988AU&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AU&quot;&gt;AU&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-21988AU\"></sup> up the vision, for it concerns the distant future.”<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-21988AV&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AV&quot;&gt;AV&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-21988AV\"></sup>",
			"27": "<sup class=\"versenum\">27 </sup>I, Daniel, was worn out. I lay exhausted<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-21989AW&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AW&quot;&gt;AW&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-21989AW\"></sup> for several days. Then I got up and went about the king’s business.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-21989AX&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AX&quot;&gt;AX&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-21989AX\"></sup> I was appalled<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-21989AY&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AY&quot;&gt;AY&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-21989AY\"></sup> by the vision; it was beyond understanding."
		},
		"9": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">9 </span>In the first year of Darius<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-21990A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-21990A\"></sup> son of Xerxes<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-21990B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-21990B\"></sup> (a Mede by descent), who was made ruler over the Babylonian kingdom—",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>in the first year of his reign, I, Daniel, understood from the Scriptures, according to the word of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> given to Jeremiah the prophet, that the desolation of Jerusalem would last seventy<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-21991C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-21991C\"></sup> years.",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>So I turned to the Lord God and pleaded with him in prayer and petition, in fasting,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-21992D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-21992D\"></sup> and in sackcloth and ashes.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-21992E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-21992E\"></sup>",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>I prayed to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> my God and confessed:<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-21993F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-21993F\"></sup>“Lord, the great and awesome God,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-21993G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-21993G\"></sup> who keeps his covenant of love<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-21993H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-21993H\"></sup> with those who love him and keep his commandments,",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>we have sinned<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-21994I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-21994I\"></sup> and done wrong.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-21994J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-21994J\"></sup> We have been wicked and have rebelled; we have turned away<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-21994K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-21994K\"></sup> from your commands and laws.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-21994L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-21994L\"></sup>",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>We have not listened<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-21995M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-21995M\"></sup> to your servants the prophets,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-21995N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-21995N\"></sup> who spoke in your name to our kings, our princes and our ancestors,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-21995O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-21995O\"></sup> and to all the people of the land.",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>“Lord, you are righteous,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-21996P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-21996P\"></sup> but this day we are covered with shame<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-21996Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-21996Q\"></sup>—the people of Judah and the inhabitants of Jerusalem and all Israel, both near and far, in all the countries where you have scattered<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-21996R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-21996R\"></sup> us because of our unfaithfulness<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-21996S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-21996S\"></sup> to you.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-21996T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-21996T\"></sup>",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>We and our kings, our princes and our ancestors are covered with shame, <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, because we have sinned against you.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-21997U&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference U&quot;&gt;U&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-21997U\"></sup>",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>The Lord our God is merciful and forgiving,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-21998V&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference V&quot;&gt;V&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-21998V\"></sup> even though we have rebelled against him;<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-21998W&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference W&quot;&gt;W&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-21998W\"></sup>",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>we have not obeyed the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> our God or kept the laws he gave us through his servants the prophets.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-21999X&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference X&quot;&gt;X&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-21999X\"></sup>",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>All Israel has transgressed<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-22000Y&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Y&quot;&gt;Y&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-22000Y\"></sup> your law<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-22000Z&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Z&quot;&gt;Z&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-22000Z\"></sup> and turned away, refusing to obey you.“Therefore the curses<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-22000AA&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AA&quot;&gt;AA&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-22000AA\"></sup> and sworn judgments<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-22000AB&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AB&quot;&gt;AB&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-22000AB\"></sup> written in the Law of Moses, the servant of God, have been poured out on us, because we have sinned<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-22000AC&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AC&quot;&gt;AC&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-22000AC\"></sup> against you.",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>You have fulfilled<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-22001AD&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AD&quot;&gt;AD&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-22001AD\"></sup> the words spoken against us and against our rulers by bringing on us great disaster.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-22001AE&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AE&quot;&gt;AE&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-22001AE\"></sup> Under the whole heaven nothing has ever been done like<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-22001AF&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AF&quot;&gt;AF&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-22001AF\"></sup> what has been done to Jerusalem.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-22001AG&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AG&quot;&gt;AG&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-22001AG\"></sup>",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>Just as it is written in the Law of Moses, all this disaster has come on us, yet we have not sought the favor of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-22002AH&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AH&quot;&gt;AH&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-22002AH\"></sup> our God by turning from our sins and giving attention to your truth.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-22002AI&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AI&quot;&gt;AI&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-22002AI\"></sup>",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>The <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> did not hesitate to bring the disaster<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-22003AJ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AJ&quot;&gt;AJ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-22003AJ\"></sup> on us, for the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> our God is righteous in everything he does;<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-22003AK&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AK&quot;&gt;AK&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-22003AK\"></sup> yet we have not obeyed him.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-22003AL&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AL&quot;&gt;AL&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-22003AL\"></sup>",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>“Now, Lord our God, who brought your people out of Egypt with a mighty hand<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-22004AM&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AM&quot;&gt;AM&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-22004AM\"></sup> and who made for yourself a name<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-22004AN&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AN&quot;&gt;AN&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-22004AN\"></sup> that endures to this day, we have sinned, we have done wrong.",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>Lord, in keeping with all your righteous acts,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-22005AO&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AO&quot;&gt;AO&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-22005AO\"></sup> turn away<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-22005AP&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AP&quot;&gt;AP&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-22005AP\"></sup> your anger and your wrath<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-22005AQ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AQ&quot;&gt;AQ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-22005AQ\"></sup> from Jerusalem,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-22005AR&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AR&quot;&gt;AR&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-22005AR\"></sup> your city, your holy hill.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-22005AS&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AS&quot;&gt;AS&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-22005AS\"></sup> Our sins and the iniquities of our ancestors have made Jerusalem and your people an object of scorn<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-22005AT&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AT&quot;&gt;AT&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-22005AT\"></sup> to all those around us.",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>“Now, our God, hear the prayers and petitions of your servant. For your sake, Lord, look with favor<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-22006AU&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AU&quot;&gt;AU&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-22006AU\"></sup> on your desolate sanctuary.",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>Give ear,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-22007AV&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AV&quot;&gt;AV&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-22007AV\"></sup> our God, and hear;<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-22007AW&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AW&quot;&gt;AW&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-22007AW\"></sup> open your eyes and see<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-22007AX&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AX&quot;&gt;AX&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-22007AX\"></sup> the desolation of the city that bears your Name.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-22007AY&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AY&quot;&gt;AY&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-22007AY\"></sup> We do not make requests of you because we are righteous, but because of your great mercy.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-22007AZ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AZ&quot;&gt;AZ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-22007AZ\"></sup>",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>Lord, listen! Lord, forgive!<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-22008BA&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BA&quot;&gt;BA&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-22008BA\"></sup> Lord, hear and act! For your sake,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-22008BB&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BB&quot;&gt;BB&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-22008BB\"></sup> my God, do not delay, because your city and your people bear your Name.”",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup>While I was speaking and praying, confessing<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-22009BC&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BC&quot;&gt;BC&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-22009BC\"></sup> my sin and the sin of my people Israel and making my request to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> my God for his holy hill<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-22009BD&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BD&quot;&gt;BD&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-22009BD\"></sup>—",
			"21": "<sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup>while I was still in prayer, Gabriel,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-22010BE&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BE&quot;&gt;BE&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-22010BE\"></sup> the man I had seen in the earlier vision, came to me in swift flight about the time of the evening sacrifice.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-22010BF&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BF&quot;&gt;BF&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-22010BF\"></sup>",
			"22": "<sup class=\"versenum\">22 </sup>He instructed me and said to me, “Daniel, I have now come to give you insight and understanding.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-22011BG&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BG&quot;&gt;BG&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-22011BG\"></sup>",
			"23": "<sup class=\"versenum\">23 </sup>As soon as you began to pray,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-22012BH&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BH&quot;&gt;BH&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-22012BH\"></sup> a word went out, which I have come to tell you, for you are highly esteemed.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-22012BI&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BI&quot;&gt;BI&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-22012BI\"></sup> Therefore, consider the word and understand the vision:<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-22012BJ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BJ&quot;&gt;BJ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-22012BJ\"></sup>",
			"24": "<sup class=\"versenum\">24 </sup>“Seventy ‘sevens’ are decreed for your people and your holy city<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-22013BK&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BK&quot;&gt;BK&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-22013BK\"></sup> to finish transgression, to put an end to sin, to atone<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-22013BL&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BL&quot;&gt;BL&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-22013BL\"></sup> for wickedness, to bring in everlasting righteousness,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-22013BM&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BM&quot;&gt;BM&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-22013BM\"></sup> to seal up vision and prophecy and to anoint the Most Holy Place.",
			"25": "<sup class=\"versenum\">25 </sup>“Know and understand this: From the time the word goes out to restore and rebuild<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-22014BN&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BN&quot;&gt;BN&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-22014BN\"></sup> Jerusalem until the Anointed One,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-22014BO&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BO&quot;&gt;BO&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-22014BO\"></sup> the ruler,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-22014BP&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BP&quot;&gt;BP&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-22014BP\"></sup> comes, there will be seven ‘sevens,’ and sixty-two ‘sevens.’ It will be rebuilt with streets and a trench, but in times of trouble.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-22014BQ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BQ&quot;&gt;BQ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-22014BQ\"></sup>",
			"26": "<sup class=\"versenum\">26 </sup>After the sixty-two ‘sevens,’ the Anointed One will be put to death<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-22015BR&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BR&quot;&gt;BR&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-22015BR\"></sup> and will have nothing. The people of the ruler who will come will destroy the city and the sanctuary. The end will come like a flood:<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-22015BS&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BS&quot;&gt;BS&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-22015BS\"></sup> War will continue until the end, and desolations<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-22015BT&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BT&quot;&gt;BT&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-22015BT\"></sup> have been decreed.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-22015BU&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BU&quot;&gt;BU&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-22015BU\"></sup>",
			"27": "<sup class=\"versenum\">27 </sup>He will confirm a covenant with many for one ‘seven.’ In the middle of the ‘seven’ he will put an end to sacrifice and offering. And at the temple he will set up an abomination that causes desolation, until the end that is decreed<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-22016BV&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BV&quot;&gt;BV&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-22016BV\"></sup> is poured out on him.”"
		},
		"10": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">10 </span>In the third year of Cyrus<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-22017A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-22017A\"></sup> king of Persia, a revelation was given to Daniel (who was called Belteshazzar).<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-22017B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-22017B\"></sup> Its message was true<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-22017C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-22017C\"></sup> and it concerned a great war. The understanding of the message came to him in a vision.",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>At that time I, Daniel, mourned<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-22018D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-22018D\"></sup> for three weeks.",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>I ate no choice food; no meat or wine touched my lips;<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-22019E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-22019E\"></sup> and I used no lotions at all until the three weeks were over.",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>On the twenty-fourth day of the first month, as I was standing on the bank<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-22020F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-22020F\"></sup> of the great river, the Tigris,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-22020G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-22020G\"></sup>",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>I looked up<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-22021H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-22021H\"></sup> and there before me was a man dressed in linen,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-22021I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-22021I\"></sup> with a belt of fine gold<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-22021J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-22021J\"></sup> from Uphaz around his waist.",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>His body was like topaz,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-22022K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-22022K\"></sup> his face like lightning,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-22022L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-22022L\"></sup> his eyes like flaming torches,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-22022M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-22022M\"></sup> his arms and legs like the gleam of burnished bronze,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-22022N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-22022N\"></sup> and his voice<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-22022O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-22022O\"></sup> like the sound of a multitude.",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>I, Daniel, was the only one who saw the vision; those who were with me did not see it,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-22023P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-22023P\"></sup> but such terror overwhelmed them that they fled and hid themselves.",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>So I was left alone,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-22024Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-22024Q\"></sup> gazing at this great vision; I had no strength left,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-22024R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-22024R\"></sup> my face turned deathly pale<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-22024S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-22024S\"></sup> and I was helpless.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-22024T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-22024T\"></sup>",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>Then I heard him speaking, and as I listened to him, I fell into a deep sleep, my face to the ground.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-22025U&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference U&quot;&gt;U&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-22025U\"></sup>",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>A hand touched me<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-22026V&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference V&quot;&gt;V&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-22026V\"></sup> and set me trembling on my hands and knees.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-22026W&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference W&quot;&gt;W&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-22026W\"></sup>",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>He said, “Daniel, you who are highly esteemed,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-22027X&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference X&quot;&gt;X&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-22027X\"></sup> consider carefully the words I am about to speak to you, and stand up,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-22027Y&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Y&quot;&gt;Y&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-22027Y\"></sup> for I have now been sent to you.” And when he said this to me, I stood up trembling.",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>Then he continued, “Do not be afraid,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-22028Z&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Z&quot;&gt;Z&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-22028Z\"></sup> Daniel. Since the first day that you set your mind to gain understanding and to humble<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-22028AA&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AA&quot;&gt;AA&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-22028AA\"></sup> yourself before your God, your words<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-22028AB&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AB&quot;&gt;AB&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-22028AB\"></sup> were heard, and I have come in response to them.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-22028AC&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AC&quot;&gt;AC&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-22028AC\"></sup>",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>But the prince<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-22029AD&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AD&quot;&gt;AD&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-22029AD\"></sup> of the Persian kingdom resisted me twenty-one days. Then Michael,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-22029AE&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AE&quot;&gt;AE&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-22029AE\"></sup> one of the chief princes, came to help me, because I was detained there with the king of Persia.",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>Now I have come to explain<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-22030AF&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AF&quot;&gt;AF&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-22030AF\"></sup> to you what will happen to your people in the future,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-22030AG&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AG&quot;&gt;AG&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-22030AG\"></sup> for the vision concerns a time yet to come.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-22030AH&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AH&quot;&gt;AH&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-22030AH\"></sup>”",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>While he was saying this to me, I bowed with my face toward the ground and was speechless.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-22031AI&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AI&quot;&gt;AI&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-22031AI\"></sup>",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>Then one who looked like a man touched my lips, and I opened my mouth and began to speak.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-22032AJ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AJ&quot;&gt;AJ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-22032AJ\"></sup> I said to the one standing before me, “I am overcome with anguish<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-22032AK&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AK&quot;&gt;AK&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-22032AK\"></sup> because of the vision, my lord, and I feel very weak.",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>How can I, your servant, talk with you, my lord? My strength is gone and I can hardly breathe.”<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-22033AL&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AL&quot;&gt;AL&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-22033AL\"></sup>",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>Again the one who looked like a man touched<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-22034AM&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AM&quot;&gt;AM&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-22034AM\"></sup> me and gave me strength.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-22034AN&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AN&quot;&gt;AN&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-22034AN\"></sup>",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>“Do not be afraid, you who are highly esteemed,”<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-22035AO&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AO&quot;&gt;AO&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-22035AO\"></sup> he said. “Peace!<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-22035AP&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AP&quot;&gt;AP&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-22035AP\"></sup> Be strong now; be strong.”<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-22035AQ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AQ&quot;&gt;AQ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-22035AQ\"></sup>When he spoke to me, I was strengthened and said, “Speak, my lord, since you have given me strength.”<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-22035AR&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AR&quot;&gt;AR&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-22035AR\"></sup>",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup>So he said, “Do you know why I have come to you? Soon I will return to fight against the prince of Persia, and when I go, the prince of Greece<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-22036AS&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AS&quot;&gt;AS&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-22036AS\"></sup> will come;",
			"21": "<sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup>but first I will tell you what is written in the Book of Truth.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-22037AT&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AT&quot;&gt;AT&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-22037AT\"></sup> (No one supports me against them except Michael,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-22037AU&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AU&quot;&gt;AU&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-22037AU\"></sup> your prince."
		},
		"11": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum mid-paragraph\">11 </span><sup class=\"versenum mid-paragraph\">1 </sup>And in the first year of Darius<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-22038A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-22038A\"></sup> the Mede, I took my stand to support and protect him.)",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>“Now then, I tell you the truth:<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-22039B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-22039B\"></sup> Three more kings will arise in Persia, and then a fourth, who will be far richer than all the others. When he has gained power by his wealth, he will stir up everyone against the kingdom of Greece.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-22039C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-22039C\"></sup>",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>Then a mighty king will arise, who will rule with great power and do as he pleases.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-22040D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-22040D\"></sup>",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>After he has arisen, his empire will be broken up and parceled out toward the four winds of heaven.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-22041E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-22041E\"></sup> It will not go to his descendants, nor will it have the power he exercised, because his empire will be uprooted<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-22041F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-22041F\"></sup> and given to others.",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>“The king of the South will become strong, but one of his commanders will become even stronger than he and will rule his own kingdom with great power.",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>After some years, they will become allies. The daughter of the king of the South will go to the king of the North to make an alliance, but she will not retain her power, and he and his power will not last. In those days she will be betrayed, together with her royal escort and her father and the one who supported her.",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>“One from her family line will arise to take her place. He will attack the forces of the king of the North<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-22044G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-22044G\"></sup> and enter his fortress; he will fight against them and be victorious.",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>He will also seize their gods,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-22045H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-22045H\"></sup> their metal images and their valuable articles of silver and gold and carry them off to Egypt.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-22045I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-22045I\"></sup> For some years he will leave the king of the North alone.",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>Then the king of the North will invade the realm of the king of the South but will retreat to his own country.",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>His sons will prepare for war and assemble a great army, which will sweep on like an irresistible flood<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-22047J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-22047J\"></sup> and carry the battle as far as his fortress.",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>“Then the king of the South will march out in a rage and fight against the king of the North, who will raise a large army, but it will be defeated.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-22048K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-22048K\"></sup>",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>When the army is carried off, the king of the South will be filled with pride and will slaughter many thousands, yet he will not remain triumphant.",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>For the king of the North will muster another army, larger than the first; and after several years, he will advance with a huge army fully equipped.",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>“In those times many will rise against the king of the South. Those who are violent among your own people will rebel in fulfillment of the vision, but without success.",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>Then the king of the North will come and build up siege ramps<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-22052L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-22052L\"></sup> and will capture a fortified city. The forces of the South will be powerless to resist; even their best troops will not have the strength to stand.",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>The invader will do as he pleases;<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-22053M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-22053M\"></sup> no one will be able to stand against him.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-22053N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-22053N\"></sup> He will establish himself in the Beautiful Land and will have the power to destroy it.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-22053O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-22053O\"></sup>",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>He will determine to come with the might of his entire kingdom and will make an alliance with the king of the South. And he will give him a daughter in marriage in order to overthrow the kingdom, but his plans will not succeed<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-22054P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-22054P\"></sup> or help him.",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>Then he will turn his attention to the coastlands<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-22055Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-22055Q\"></sup> and will take many of them, but a commander will put an end to his insolence and will turn his insolence back on him.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-22055R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-22055R\"></sup>",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>After this, he will turn back toward the fortresses of his own country but will stumble and fall,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-22056S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-22056S\"></sup> to be seen no more.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-22056T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-22056T\"></sup>",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup>“His successor will send out a tax collector to maintain the royal splendor.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-22057U&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference U&quot;&gt;U&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-22057U\"></sup> In a few years, however, he will be destroyed, yet not in anger or in battle.",
			"21": "<sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup>“He will be succeeded by a contemptible<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-22058V&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference V&quot;&gt;V&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-22058V\"></sup> person who has not been given the honor of royalty.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-22058W&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference W&quot;&gt;W&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-22058W\"></sup> He will invade the kingdom when its people feel secure, and he will seize it through intrigue.",
			"22": "<sup class=\"versenum\">22 </sup>Then an overwhelming army will be swept away<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-22059X&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference X&quot;&gt;X&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-22059X\"></sup> before him; both it and a prince of the covenant will be destroyed.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-22059Y&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Y&quot;&gt;Y&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-22059Y\"></sup>",
			"23": "<sup class=\"versenum\">23 </sup>After coming to an agreement with him, he will act deceitfully,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-22060Z&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Z&quot;&gt;Z&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-22060Z\"></sup> and with only a few people he will rise to power.",
			"24": "<sup class=\"versenum\">24 </sup>When the richest provinces feel secure, he will invade them and will achieve what neither his fathers nor his forefathers did. He will distribute plunder, loot and wealth among his followers.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-22061AA&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AA&quot;&gt;AA&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-22061AA\"></sup> He will plot the overthrow of fortresses—but only for a time.",
			"25": "<sup class=\"versenum\">25 </sup>“With a large army he will stir up his strength and courage against the king of the South. The king of the South will wage war with a large and very powerful army, but he will not be able to stand because of the plots devised against him.",
			"26": "<sup class=\"versenum\">26 </sup>Those who eat from the king’s provisions will try to destroy him; his army will be swept away, and many will fall in battle.",
			"27": "<sup class=\"versenum\">27 </sup>The two kings, with their hearts bent on evil,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-22064AB&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AB&quot;&gt;AB&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-22064AB\"></sup> will sit at the same table and lie<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-22064AC&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AC&quot;&gt;AC&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-22064AC\"></sup> to each other, but to no avail, because an end will still come at the appointed time.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-22064AD&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AD&quot;&gt;AD&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-22064AD\"></sup>",
			"28": "<sup class=\"versenum\">28 </sup>The king of the North will return to his own country with great wealth, but his heart will be set against the holy covenant. He will take action against it and then return to his own country.",
			"29": "<sup class=\"versenum\">29 </sup>“At the appointed time he will invade the South again, but this time the outcome will be different from what it was before.",
			"30": "<sup class=\"versenum\">30 </sup>Ships of the western coastlands<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-22067AE&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AE&quot;&gt;AE&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-22067AE\"></sup> will oppose him, and he will lose heart.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-22067AF&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AF&quot;&gt;AF&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-22067AF\"></sup> Then he will turn back and vent his fury<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-22067AG&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AG&quot;&gt;AG&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-22067AG\"></sup> against the holy covenant. He will return and show favor to those who forsake the holy covenant.",
			"31": "<sup class=\"versenum\">31 </sup>“His armed forces will rise up to desecrate the temple fortress and will abolish the daily sacrifice.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-22068AH&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AH&quot;&gt;AH&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-22068AH\"></sup> Then they will set up the abomination that causes desolation.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-22068AI&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AI&quot;&gt;AI&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-22068AI\"></sup>",
			"32": "<sup class=\"versenum\">32 </sup>With flattery he will corrupt those who have violated the covenant, but the people who know their God will firmly resist<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-22069AJ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AJ&quot;&gt;AJ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-22069AJ\"></sup> him.",
			"33": "<sup class=\"versenum\">33 </sup>“Those who are wise will instruct<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-22070AK&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AK&quot;&gt;AK&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-22070AK\"></sup> many, though for a time they will fall by the sword or be burned or captured or plundered.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-22070AL&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AL&quot;&gt;AL&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-22070AL\"></sup>",
			"34": "<sup class=\"versenum\">34 </sup>When they fall, they will receive a little help, and many who are not sincere<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-22071AM&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AM&quot;&gt;AM&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-22071AM\"></sup> will join them.",
			"35": "<sup class=\"versenum\">35 </sup>Some of the wise will stumble, so that they may be refined,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-22072AN&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AN&quot;&gt;AN&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-22072AN\"></sup> purified and made spotless until the time of the end, for it will still come at the appointed time.",
			"36": "<sup class=\"versenum\">36 </sup>“The king will do as he pleases. He will exalt and magnify himself<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-22073AO&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AO&quot;&gt;AO&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-22073AO\"></sup> above every god and will say unheard-of things<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-22073AP&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AP&quot;&gt;AP&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-22073AP\"></sup> against the God of gods.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-22073AQ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AQ&quot;&gt;AQ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-22073AQ\"></sup> He will be successful until the time of wrath<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-22073AR&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AR&quot;&gt;AR&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-22073AR\"></sup> is completed, for what has been determined must take place.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-22073AS&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AS&quot;&gt;AS&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-22073AS\"></sup>",
			"37": "<sup class=\"versenum\">37 </sup>He will show no regard for the gods of his ancestors or for the one desired by women, nor will he regard any god, but will exalt himself above them all.",
			"38": "<sup class=\"versenum\">38 </sup>Instead of them, he will honor a god of fortresses; a god unknown to his ancestors he will honor with gold and silver, with precious stones and costly gifts.",
			"39": "<sup class=\"versenum\">39 </sup>He will attack the mightiest fortresses with the help of a foreign god and will greatly honor those who acknowledge him. He will make them rulers over many people and will distribute the land at a price.",
			"40": "<sup class=\"versenum\">40 </sup>“At the time of the end the king of the South<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-22077AT&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AT&quot;&gt;AT&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-22077AT\"></sup> will engage him in battle, and the king of the North will storm<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-22077AU&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AU&quot;&gt;AU&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-22077AU\"></sup> out against him with chariots and cavalry and a great fleet of ships. He will invade many countries and sweep through them like a flood.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-22077AV&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AV&quot;&gt;AV&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-22077AV\"></sup>",
			"41": "<sup class=\"versenum\">41 </sup>He will also invade the Beautiful Land.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-22078AW&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AW&quot;&gt;AW&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-22078AW\"></sup> Many countries will fall, but Edom,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-22078AX&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AX&quot;&gt;AX&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-22078AX\"></sup> Moab<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-22078AY&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AY&quot;&gt;AY&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-22078AY\"></sup> and the leaders of Ammon will be delivered from his hand.",
			"42": "<sup class=\"versenum\">42 </sup>He will extend his power over many countries; Egypt will not escape.",
			"43": "<sup class=\"versenum\">43 </sup>He will gain control of the treasures of gold and silver and all the riches of Egypt,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-22080AZ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AZ&quot;&gt;AZ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-22080AZ\"></sup> with the Libyans<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-22080BA&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BA&quot;&gt;BA&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-22080BA\"></sup> and Cushites in submission.",
			"44": "<sup class=\"versenum\">44 </sup>But reports from the east and the north will alarm him, and he will set out in a great rage to destroy and annihilate many.",
			"45": "<sup class=\"versenum\">45 </sup>He will pitch his royal tents between the seas at the beautiful holy mountain.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-22082BB&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BB&quot;&gt;BB&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-22082BB\"></sup> Yet he will come to his end, and no one will help him."
		},
		"12": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">12 </span>“At that time Michael,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-22083A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-22083A\"></sup> the great prince who protects your people, will arise. There will be a time of distress<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-22083B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-22083B\"></sup> such as has not happened from the beginning of nations until then. But at that time your people—everyone whose name is found written in the book<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-22083C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-22083C\"></sup>—will be delivered.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-22083D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-22083D\"></sup>",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>Multitudes who sleep in the dust of the earth will awake:<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-22084E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-22084E\"></sup> some to everlasting life, others to shame and everlasting contempt.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-22084F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-22084F\"></sup>",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>Those who are wise<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-22085G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-22085G\"></sup> will shine<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-22085H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-22085H\"></sup> like the brightness of the heavens, and those who lead many to righteousness,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-22085I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-22085I\"></sup> like the stars for ever and ever.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-22085J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-22085J\"></sup>",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>But you, Daniel, roll up and seal<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-22086K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-22086K\"></sup> the words of the scroll until the time of the end.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-22086L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-22086L\"></sup> Many will go here and there<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-22086M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-22086M\"></sup> to increase knowledge.”",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>Then I, Daniel, looked, and there before me stood two others, one on this bank of the river and one on the opposite bank.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-22087N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-22087N\"></sup>",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>One of them said to the man clothed in linen,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-22088O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-22088O\"></sup> who was above the waters of the river, “How long will it be before these astonishing things are fulfilled?”<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-22088P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-22088P\"></sup>",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>The man clothed in linen, who was above the waters of the river, lifted his right hand<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-22089Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-22089Q\"></sup> and his left hand toward heaven, and I heard him swear by him who lives forever,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-22089R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-22089R\"></sup> saying, “It will be for a time, times and half a time.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-22089S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-22089S\"></sup> When the power of the holy people<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-22089T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-22089T\"></sup> has been finally broken, all these things will be completed.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-22089U&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference U&quot;&gt;U&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-22089U\"></sup>”",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>I heard, but I did not understand. So I asked, “My lord, what will the outcome of all this be?”",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>He replied, “Go your way, Daniel, because the words are rolled up and sealed<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-22091V&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference V&quot;&gt;V&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-22091V\"></sup> until the time of the end.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-22091W&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference W&quot;&gt;W&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-22091W\"></sup>",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>Many will be purified, made spotless and refined,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-22092X&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference X&quot;&gt;X&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-22092X\"></sup> but the wicked will continue to be wicked.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-22092Y&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Y&quot;&gt;Y&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-22092Y\"></sup> None of the wicked will understand, but those who are wise will understand.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-22092Z&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Z&quot;&gt;Z&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-22092Z\"></sup>",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>“From the time that the daily sacrifice<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-22093AA&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AA&quot;&gt;AA&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-22093AA\"></sup> is abolished and the abomination that causes desolation<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-22093AB&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AB&quot;&gt;AB&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-22093AB\"></sup> is set up, there will be 1,290 days.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-22093AC&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AC&quot;&gt;AC&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-22093AC\"></sup>",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>Blessed is the one who waits<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-22094AD&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AD&quot;&gt;AD&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-22094AD\"></sup> for and reaches the end of the 1,335 days.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-22094AE&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AE&quot;&gt;AE&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-22094AE\"></sup>",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>“As for you, go your way till the end.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-22095AF&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AF&quot;&gt;AF&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-22095AF\"></sup> You will rest,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-22095AG&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AG&quot;&gt;AG&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-22095AG\"></sup> and then at the end of the days you will rise to receive your allotted inheritance.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-22095AH&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AH&quot;&gt;AH&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-22095AH\"></sup>”"
		}
	}
};
module.exports = book;